L(x)=\int_{1}^x {1\over t} dt 
L(x)
ln(x)
ln(x)
e^x
l(x)=s_n={1 \over x}
y=1/t
dt = -\dfrac{dy}{y^2}
n \in \mathbb{N}
L(1/x) = \int_1^{1/x} \dfrac1t dt
L(1/x) = \int_1^x y\left( -\dfrac{dy}{y^2} \right) = - \int_1^x \dfrac{dy}y = - L(x)
s_{2n} - s_n = \dfrac1{n+1} + \cdots + \dfrac1{2n} > \dfrac1{2n} + \dfrac1{2n} + \cdots + \dfrac1{2n} = \dfrac12
\int_1^x \dfrac{dt}t > \int_1^2 \dfrac{dt}2 + \int_2^3 \dfrac{dt}3 + \cdots + \int_{\lfloor x \rfloor - 1}^{\lfloor x \rfloor} \dfrac{dt}{\lfloor x \rfloor} = \dfrac12 + \dfrac13 + \cdots + \dfrac1{\lfloor x \rfloor} = s_{\lfloor x \rfloor} - 1
s=1/t
x>0
L(\frac1x)=-L(x)
[L(\frac1x)]^{\prime}=L^{\prime}(\frac1x)(\frac1x)^{\prime}=x\frac{-1}{x^2}=-\frac1x=(-L(x))^{\prime}
L\left(\frac{1}{x}\right):=\int_1^{1/x}\frac{dt}{t}\;\;,\;\;u:=\frac{1}{t}\,\,,\,du=-\frac{1}{t^2}dt=-u^2\,dt\Longrightarrow
L\left(\frac{1}{x}\right)=\int_1^x-\frac{du}{u^2}\cdot u=-\int^x_1\frac{du}{u}=-L(x)
|s_m-s_n|=\left|\frac{1}{n+1}+\frac{1}{n+2}+\ldots +\frac{1}{m}\right|\geq \frac{m-n}{m}=1-\frac{n}{m}
\,n\,
\,m\to\infty\,
